1. Find all the files which are greater than 4kb and delete it
We can use the command-
Syntax: find . -type f -size +4k -delete
ex: In the below example, 
-	Step1: I have highlighted the files which are greater than 4kb using the command “ls -lt”
-	Step2: Use the command “find .-type f -size +4k -delete” to delete the files larger than 4kb
-	Step3: Now using the command “ls -lt” I can see the files having more than 4kb have been deleted.
 




2. Find all the files with .txt and change the permission to 777
We can use the following command-
Syntax: find . -type f -name "*.txt" | xargs chmod 777
ex: Below example, 
-	Step1: I used “ls -lt” to check what all the textfiles present in.
-	Step2: Then I executed the command “find . -type f -name “*.txt” | xargs chmod 777
-	Step3: now, we can see the textfiles having 777 permission using “ls -lt”
 
 

